<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-716] Reader.readLine() consumes too many characters.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-716</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;br/&gt;
import java.io.FileReader&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;f=new FileReader(inputFile)&lt;br/&gt;
header=f.readLine()&lt;br/&gt;
println &quot;==${header}==&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
f.readLines().each {&lt;br/&gt;
  println &quot;###&quot;&lt;ins&gt;it&lt;/ins&gt;&quot;###&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;only works if &quot;f&quot; is decorated with a BufferedReader&lt;br/&gt;
 f=new BufferedReader(new FileReader(inputFile))&lt;br/&gt;
otherwise &quot;f&quot; misses some lines.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cause:&lt;br/&gt;
DefaultGroovyMethods.readLine constructs BufferedReader of &quot;self&quot;, if &quot;self&quot;  is not an instance of BufferedReader.&lt;br/&gt;
BufferedReader does some readahead which &quot;destroys&quot; the FileReader contents.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Groovy B9&lt;br/&gt;
J2SE 1.5.0_1&lt;br/&gt;
WinXP-SP2</environment>
