                            <comment id="14461030" author="wangbin" created="Sun, 12 Jun 2005 23:59:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is because we can&apos;t wrap reader with BufferedReader more than one time. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, I suggest, we should not support readLine(Reader) default method, and we should only support default method readLine(BufferedRead). &lt;br/&gt;
If so, we can let user make sure only decorate reader with BufferedRead only one time &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The same thing exists in readLine(InputStream stream) which method should not be supported &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Below is my java code &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public class ReaderTest { &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException { &lt;br/&gt;
FileReader r = new FileReader(&quot;E:/groovy/demo.txt&quot;); &lt;br/&gt;
BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(r); &lt;br/&gt;
String line = br.readLine(); &lt;br/&gt;
System.out.println(line); &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;line = br.readLine(); &lt;br/&gt;
System.out.println(line); &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BufferedReader br2 = new BufferedReader(r); &lt;br/&gt;
line = br2.readLine(); &lt;br/&gt;
System.out.println(line); &lt;br/&gt;
} &lt;br/&gt;
} &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From the output, we can see, the third line also is &quot;null&quot;. &lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;below it the current code for readLine(Read): &lt;br/&gt;
    public static String readLine(Reader self) throws IOException { &lt;br/&gt;
        BufferedReader br = null; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        if (self instanceof BufferedReader) &lt;/p&gt;
{ 
            br = (BufferedReader) self; 
        }
&lt;p&gt; else &lt;/p&gt;
{ 
            br = new BufferedReader(self); 
        }
&lt;p&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
        return br.readLine(); &lt;br/&gt;
    } &lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14461170" author="blackdrag" created="Thu, 7 Jul 2005 05:16:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;rather than removing the readline method we could try to do some magic with mark/reset, or implement a readline method of our own. But doing a readline method basing on read() may be slow.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
